C. The Iambic Octonarius (= Greek Iambic Tetrameter Acatalectic).

(a) This is a line of eight iambic or quasi-iambic feet.

(b) The final soot must be a pure iambus, though syllaba anceps may occur at the end of the line (i. e. a pyrrhic may there be reckoned as an iambus).
